  "author_information": "Herman Melville (1819-1891) was an American novelist, short story writer, and poet. Best known for Moby-Dick, his works often explore complex themes of good and evil, the individual’s struggle against the universe, and the nature of humanity.",
  "interesting_fact": "Moby-Dick was not initially well-received, and its recognition as a masterpiece came long after Melville’s death. The novel draws from Melville’s own experiences at sea and the true story of the whaleship Essex, which was sunk by a sperm whale in 1820, providing a rich blend of adventure, philosophy, and detailed whaling knowledge."
